# 12298b0decb247208ce77f7dc7815df0
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:23
msgid "Understanding |TS| Log Files"
msgstr ""

# 9023887300d24f81845da891dd093b2a
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:25
msgid ""
"|TS| records information about every transaction (or request) it "
"processes and every error it detects in log files. |TS| keeps three types"
" of log files:"
msgstr ""

# f435aa7a0eab4dbb81b2cd147d457267
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:28
msgid ""
"*Error log files* record information about why a particular transaction "
"was in error."
msgstr ""

# 6119dd6fcc3d47eaabea7868bcc7ac06
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:31
msgid ""
"*Event log files* (also called *access log files*) record information "
"about the state of each transaction Traffic Server processes."
msgstr ""

# 040d719ae2ee4576900c1d80d3ac2133
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:35
msgid ""
"*System log files* record system information, including messages about "
"the state of Traffic Server and errors/warnings it produces. This kind of"
" information might include a note that event log files were rolled, a "
"warning that cluster communication timed out, or an error indicating that"
" Traffic Server was restarted."
msgstr ""

# c32efc2c2d5a4734b4f37fccbf1d125c
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:41
msgid ""
"All system information messages are logged with the system-wide logging "
"facility :manpage:`syslog` under the daemon facility. The "
":manpage:`syslog.conf(5)` configuration file (stored in the ``/etc`` "
"directory) specifies where these messages are logged. A typical location "
"is ``/var/log/messages`` (Linux)."
msgstr ""

# efc5e78d783a402cbc9c78bcbe4f77bf
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:47
msgid ""
"The :manpage:`syslog(8)` process works on a system-wide basis, so it "
"serves as the single repository for messages from all Traffic Server "
"processes (including :program:`traffic_server`, "
":program:`traffic_manager`, and :program:`traffic_cop`)."
msgstr ""

# 0b444fe06c8e4ee2a28796cb107f7c97
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:52
msgid ""
"System information logs observe a static format. Each log entry in the "
"log contains information about the date and time the error was logged, "
"the hostname of the Traffic Server that reported the error, and a "
"description of the error or warning."
msgstr ""

# 7ab6096b7a334382bf99956aa3a5330a
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:57
msgid ""
"Refer to :ref:`traffic-server-error-messages` for a list of the messages "
"logged by Traffic Server."
msgstr ""

# 5dd7ec6d92f342bd8f1302fdda642a65
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:60
msgid ""
"By default, |TS| creates both error and event log files and records "
"system information in system log files. You can disable event logging "
"and/or error logging by setting the configuration variable "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.log.logging_enabled` in :file:`records.config` to "
"one of the following values:"
msgstr ""

# ebdc40bed5cd4b71831e94738525faa3
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:67
msgid "Value"
msgstr ""

# e94587068bf446d3813a20be3b622a63
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:67
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

# 6367a3bcdb044661b2ceba385f53fea8
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:69
msgid "``0``"
msgstr ""

# 5064423849f442b6a90b0d1100082a8f
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:69
msgid "Disable both event and error logging."
msgstr ""

# 38dd850fec6f47ce948c7d9b3afe5998
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:70
msgid "``1``"
msgstr ""

# f12548abc4e6477fbda441f7611e03e5
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:70
msgid "Enable error logging only."
msgstr ""

# 3ccbf7f2e5674a61bdcd1622bd51b58a
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:71
msgid "``2``"
msgstr ""

# ae00a539973941f7b44a287bd2fee196
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:71
msgid "Enable event logging only."
msgstr ""

# 63cc429e93a040b88a908e163f9aad2b
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:72
msgid "``3``"
msgstr ""

# 13d19ad6f40349149d5784811a4bc01b
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:72
msgid "Enable both event and error logging."
msgstr ""

# 6d4c8a8213bc421a861427e3134bc05d
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/logging/understanding.en.rst:75
msgid ""
"By analyzing the log files, you can determine how many people use the "
"|TS| cache, how much information each person requested, what pages are "
"most popular, and so on. |TS| supports several standard log file formats,"
" such as Squid and Netscape, as well as user-defined custom formats. You "
"can analyze the standard format log files with off-the-shelf analysis "
"packages. To help with log file analysis, you can separate log files so "
"they contain information specific to protocol or hosts. You can also "
"configure |TS| to roll log files automatically at specific intervals "
"during the day or when they reach a certain size."
msgstr ""

